snippet.title: Exterior Angles of a Regular Polygon - MathHelp.com
snippet.description: For a complete lesson on exterior angles of a regular polygon, go to http://www.MathHelp.com - 1000+ online math lessons featuring a personal math teacher inside every lesson! In this lesson, students learn the definition of a regular polygon, as well as the following formulas related to regular polygons. The measure of each interior angle of a regular polygon is always 180(n - 2)/n degrees, where n represents the number of sides of the polygon. The measure of each exterior angle of a regular polygon is 360/n degrees. Students are then asked to solve problems using these formulas.
